FLUX:

Fluxul actual: 1. Front-end → Container 1 (Javalin REST API)
• Imaginea este trimisă prin REST API. 2. Container 1 → Container 2 (JMS Topic)
• Javalin publică imaginea ca mesaj binar pe JMS Topic. 3. Container 3 (EJB MDB)
• Se abonează la JMS Topic.
• Este și client Java RMI pentru Container 4 și 5 (RMI Servers) → aici se face zoom-ul imaginii. 4. Container 4 & 5 (Java RMI Servers)
• Procesează imaginea (zoom) și returnează rezultatul către MDB din container 3. 5. Container 3 → Container 6 (MySQL BLOB)
• MDB salvează imaginea modificată în MySQL. 6. Container 6 → Node.js REST API
• Node.js expune endpoint-uri pentru a descărca imaginea BMP și a afișa SNMP. 7. Notificare Front-end
• Container 1 notifică front-end-ul prin WebSocket/REST că imaginea este gata și redirecționează către URL-ul Node.js pentru descărcare.

Semester Assignment
Deadline - YYYY/MM/dd HH:mm: 2024/01/15 (Current Year/01/15 23:50 GMT+2)
Problem description: "Create 6 Docker containers from Docker Image: https://hub.docker.com/r/critoma/linux-u20-dev-security-ism
for zooming in/out a large BMP picture. Please draw the architecture in draw.io/diagrams.net/Visio/ or equivalent Tools and implement the following requirements.

The picture is received from the Front-end (Plain JS/CSS/HTML or Angular or Vue.js or REACT) into the 1st container Back-End via REST API (Javalin or Jakarta EE Servlet REST API) and then is published as binary message into a JMS Topic from the 2nd container which is a MoM JMS Broker. In the 3rd container a Jakarta EE EJB MDB is subscribed to the 2nd container JMS Topic and it is also Java RMI Client for 2 Java RMI Servers which are running in the 4th and 5th containers. When the BMP picture is ready, then it is stored in 6th container MySQL DB as BLOB - Binary Large Object. The 6th container has 2 DBs - one MongoDB for collecting SNMP values from all the nodes regarding OS name, CPU and RAM usage and a MySQL DB for storing modified pictures. All these are exposed through node.js JS Express REST Endpoints - one for SNMP values display and one for BMP picture rendering. When the zoomed BMP pic is inserted in the MySQL, then the 1st container via REST API/WebSocket is notifying the front-end with HTTP redirection to the node.js URL for downloading the picture. As a list there are the following containers:

Front-end (JS, Angular, Vue.js) -> load pic&params(Zoom In/Out, +/- %) via REST API
-> C01: Java Javalin/Apache Tomcat 10 Microserv + JMS Client Publisher
-> C02: Apache TomEE 10 w JMS Broker - Topic & Queues
-> C03: Apache TomEE 10 w EJB Client MDB & RMI Client <- zoom pics united into DB via REST API & JMS Client Publisher in Topic/Queue that the job is done
-> C04, C05: Apache TomEE 10 w RMI Server objects
<- C01: Notification that the pic is ready => in the front-end with link for download from node.js C06
-> C06: REST API in node.js w MongoDB with 2 REST API endpoints interfaces: 1 for DB access and 1 for Web Access

"

Upload and packiging: "The ZIP file has the source code files + _.sh/_.bat file for compiling and running the samples. The ZIP filename rule will have DAD2023_A01_SURNAME_FirstName1_FirstName2.zip". The upload is available through online.ase.ro

#COMMANDS for myself

1. docker build --platform=linux/amd64 -t javalin-app .
2. docker run -d --platform=linux/amd64 -p 7001:7000 --name java_javalin_app javalin-app

3. docker build -f ./Dockerfile.react -t react-app .
4. docker run -d -p 3000:3000 --name react react-app

5. docker build -f ./Dockerfile.snmp -t snmp-agent .
6. docker run -d --name snmpd -p 161:161/udp snmp-agent
   test on local:
   snmpwalk -v2c -c public localhost:161
   snmpwalk -v2c -c public localhost:161 1.3.6.1.2.1.1.3

# Note

For teacher: just type in the root of this folder the next command:
:$ docker compose up -d
This will build and run all the 6 containers needed for the project.

##Implement the Complete Workflow
Image upload flow from React → Java Javalin → JMS → EJB MDB → RMI servers → MySQL
Notification system back to front-end when processing is complete
Integration between all 6 containers

##Testing and Integration
Test the complete image processing pipeline
Verify SNMP data collection
Test REST API endpoints

Pentur JAVA ( Maven ) un fel de npm in nodejs ( e nevoie de fisierul pom.xml in radacina proiectului )
mvn dependency:copy-dependencies
